TY  - JOUR
AU  - Ali, S Nageeb
AU  - Haghpanah, Nima
AU  - Lin, Xiao
AU  - Siegel, Ron
T1  - How to Sell Hard Information*
PY  - 2022
Y1  - 2022/02/01
DO  - 10.1093/qje/qjab024
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 137
IS  - 1
SP  - 619
EP  - 678
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - The seller of an asset has the option to buy hard information about the value of the asset from an intermediary. The seller can then disclose this information before selling the asset in a competitive market. We study how the intermediary designs and sells hard information to robustly maximize the intermediary's revenue across all equilibria. Even though the intermediary could use an accurate test that reveals the asset’s value, we show that robust revenue maximization leads to a noisy test with a continuum of possible scores. In addition, the intermediary always charges the seller for disclosing the test score to the market, but not necessarily for running the test. This enables the intermediary to robustly appropriate a significant share of the surplus resulting from the asset sale.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/qje/qjab024
ER  - 



